{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QNXye4mLP6SS5Qj1DUWUQK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have everything I need. Let me plan the steps:\n\n1. **TLS Secret for DB Console**: Generate a self-signed cert for `crdb-ui.example.com` and create a TLS secret in the `cockroachdb` namespace (or `ingress-nginx` namespace - typically in the same namespace as the Ingress).\n\n2. **Ingress for DB Console**: Create an Ingress resource in `cockroachdb` namespace:\n   - Host: `crdb-ui.example.com`\n   - TLS: reference the TLS secret\n   - Backend: `crdb-cluster-public:8080`\n   - IngressClass: nginx\n\n3. **TCP ConfigMap**: Create `tcp-services` ConfigMap in `ingress-nginx` namespace to expose the CockroachDB SQL port 26257.\n\n4. **Patch ingress-nginx controller**: Add the TCP services configmap reference to the controller arguments.\n\n5. **Patch ingress-nginx-controller Service**: Add port 26257 to expose it externally.\n\nThe TLS secret needs to live in the same namespace as the Ingress resource, so I'll place both in the `cockroachdb` namespace. Now I'm generating a self-signed certificate for the TLS configuration.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":538,"cache_read_input_tokens":32620,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":538},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b98e9e04-0b12-4ff9-aafa-a9747a46b310","uuid":"6e2e2d04-a280-4f6c-b0a3-211575879f57","request_id":"req_011CcMPsizrQT4t8zevnfCxf"}
